Another technique that can provide information regarding the protein adsorption processes as well as the structure of the adsorbed protein layer is ellipsometry. Ellipsometry is an optical technique that measures changes in the reflectance and phase difference between the parallel (R
P) and perpendicular (R
S) components of a polarized light beam upon reflection from a surface. Using Eq. (2.2),
