Depending on the electronic properties of the materials tested, different optical models can be applied to the data collected by ellipsometry [34, 44]. In the simplest case, when the layers can be considered transparent and homogeneous, the refractive index (n) as a function of the wavelength (λ) can be described using a classical Cauchy model (Eq. 2.3):
